The paper deals with the analysis and design of communication systems, specifically MIMO channels, in the presence of selective fading. This falls under the information theory (cs.IT) and networking and internet architecture (cs.NI) categories. The paper also discusses the optimization of the diversity-multiplexing tradeoff, which is a system-level performance metric, making it relevant to the systems and control (cs.SY) category. Additionally, the paper mentions code design, which is a topic in multimedia (cs.MM) and communication (cs.COM) categories.
